  "locked_theoretical_statement": "The IO3 rerun does not provide clean support for the simple code-availability hypothesis. Instead, the emerging evidence suggests a stronger uptake mechanism: executable evidence improves reconstruction only when the agent grounds its workflow in real data and avoids synthetic substitution. Code availability alone is insufficient. Mechanism: IO -> material availability; agent uptake -> evidence use; ECRF -> reconstruction fidelity."
